# ─── Notion Integration ───
# Follow these steps to connect your Notion databases:
#
# 1. Go to https://www.notion.so/my-integrations and create a new integration
#    - Name: "Sentoe Blog"
#    - Associated workspace: your workspace
#    - Copy the "Internal Integration Secret" → paste below as NOTION_API_KEY
#
# 2. Create two databases in Notion:
#
#    Posts Database fields:
#    - Title        (title)       — Article title
#    - Slug         (text)        — URL path, e.g. "gpt-product-analysis"
#    - Language     (select)      — Options: zh, en
#    - Status       (select)      — Options: Draft, Published
#    - Category     (select)      — Options: AI Product Analysis, Industry Insights, Project Review, Reading Notes
#    - Tags         (multi-select) — Free-form tags
#    - Summary      (text)        — 120 chars max
#    - Date         (date)        — Publish date
#    - Cover        (files)       — Cover image
#
#    Projects Database fields:
#    - Name         (title)       — Project name
#    - Description  (text)        — One-line description
#    - Language     (select)      — Options: zh, en
#    - Role         (text)        — Your role
#    - Tags         (multi-select) — Tech/tool tags
#    - Cover        (files)       — Cover image
#    - Link         (url)         — Demo URL
#    - GitHub       (url)         — GitHub repo URL
#    - Order        (number)      — Sort order (1, 2, 3...)
#
# 3. Share each database with your integration:
#    - Open the database in Notion
#    - Click "..." menu → "Connections" → Add your integration
#
# 4. Get the database IDs:
#    - Open the database as a full page in Notion
#    - The URL looks like: https://notion.so/YOUR_WORKSPACE/DATABASE_ID?v=...
#    - Copy the DATABASE_ID part (32 hex chars)
#
# 5. Copy this file to .env.local and fill in the values:
#    cp .env.example .env.local

NOTION_API_KEY=
NOTION_POSTS_DB_ID=
NOTION_PROJECTS_DB_ID=
NOTION_GALLERY_DB_ID=
# ─── Umami Analytics (optional) ───
# NEXT_PUBLIC_UMAMI_WEBSITE_ID=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_UMAMI_SRC=
